Delta hit Israel in June, just as the country began to reap the benefits of one of the world's fastest vaccine roll-outs.  With an open economy and most curbs scrapped, Israel went from single-digit daily infections and zero deaths to around 7,500 daily cases last week, 600 people hospitalized in serious condition and more than 150 people dying in that week alone.
